          <p>Neptune is the eighth and most distant planet from the Sun. This ice giant is famous for its stunning deep blue color, the fastest winds in the solar system reaching 2,100 km/h, and being the first planet discovered through mathematical prediction. With 16 known moons including the remarkable retrograde Triton, mysterious dark storms, and a dynamic atmosphere despite its distance from the Sun, Neptune stands as one of the solar system's most enigmatic worlds.</p>
